................................................................. 42\nVI. Reports................................................................................................................................................... 44\nFederal Financial Reports ........................................................................................................................ 44\nProgram Progress Reports ...................................................................................................................... 45\nContact points to obtain technical assistance and report violations...................................................... 47 ii 2016 COPS Office Anti-Heroin Task Force Program (AHTF) Award Owner’s Manual VII. When the Award Period Has Ended ..................................................................................................... 48\nFinal Federal Financial Report (SF-425) .................................................................................................. 48\nFinal Program Progress (Closeout) Report .............................................................................................. 48\nEquipment disposition ............................................................................................................................ 49\nVIII. Conclusion............................................................................................................................................ 50\nAppendices.................................................................................................................................................. 51\nAppendix A. List of Source Documents ................................................................................................... 51\nAppendix B. Assurances and Certifications ............................................................................................. 52\nAppendix C. Community policing defined ............................................................................................... 60\nAppendix D. COPS Office Anti-Heroin Task Force (AHTF) program file management:\nDocuments to maintain in AHTF award file ............................................................................................ 67\nAppendix E. Whistleblower protection (41 U.S.C. 4712) ........................................................................ 70\nAppendix F. 2 CFR Appendix II to Part 200:\nContract provisions for nonfederal entity contracts under federal awards ........................................... 73\nAppendix G. Remittance of Interest Earned Amounts............................................................................ 75\nGlossary of Terms........................................................................................................................................ 76\nCOPS Office Resources ................................................................................................................................ 80 iii 2016 COPS Office Anti-Heroin Task Force Program (AHTF) Award Owner’s Manual Getting Started\nCongratulations on receiving an award from the U.S. Department of Justice (DOJ), Office of Community Oriented\nPolicing Services (COPS Office). The 2016 COPS Office Anti-Heroin Task Force Program (AHTF) is designed to\nadvance public safety by providing funds to state law enforcement agencies with high rates of primary\ntreatment admissions for heroin and other opioids. This AHTF funding must be used for investigative purposes\nto locate or investigate, through statewide collaboration, illicit activities, including activities related to the\ndistribution of heroin or unlawful distribution of prescriptive opioids and unlawful diversion and distribution of\nprescriptive opioids."
